President Muhammadu Buhari has summoned Abubakar Aliyu, minister of power, for a meeting at the presidential villa. The president is expected to discuss the erratic power supply experienced across the country in recent weeks. Buhari also called for a meeting with Hope Uzodimma, governor of Imo state, and Doyin Salami, his chief economic adviser. Garba Shehu, senior special assistant to the president on media and publicity, announced the development in a statement on Monday. More to followâ€¦